channel.title: Compile Errors? HELP ++Rep
channel.description:
Alright so ive added this code as told to in a tutorial
-
[code]int voteTime = (int)(p.voteDelay - System.currentTimeMillis() + p.voteLength); if(voteTime > 86400000 || voteTime < 0){ voteTime = 0; }[/code]
UNDER
[code]p.playerName = p.playerName2; int tbTime = (int)(p.teleBlockDelay - System.currentTimeMillis() + p.teleBlockLength); if(tbTime > 300000 || tbTime < 0){ tbTime = 0; }[/code]
This is in playersave.java and im wondering why im getting the following compiling errors
[code]source\server\model\players\PlayerSave.java:102: incompatible types found : long required: java.lang.String p.voteDelay = System.currentTime Millis();
^ source\server\model\players\PlayerSave.java:103: incompatible types found : int required: java.lang.String p.voteLength = Integer.parseInt( token2); ^
source\server\model\players\PlayerSave.java:410: operator - cannot be applied to java.lang.String,long int voteTime = (int)(p.voteDelay - System.currentTimeMillis() + p.voteLength); ^ source\server\model\players\PlayerSave.java:410: inconvertible types found : java.lang.String required: int int voteTime = (int)(p.voteDelay - System.currentTimeMillis() + p.voteLength); ^ Note: Some input files use unchecked or unsafe operations. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. 4 errors Press any key to continue . . .[/code]
This is Holding me Back from Making 2 spins Per Day for my squeal of fortune.
THANKS FOR READING im willing to give all my ++rep for making this work as its one of my favourite peices of work
thanks -hack3r-
